WEBVTT

00:02.400 --> 00:03.765
* HERE THEY COMING WITH
THEIR GUNS, GUNS, GUNS, GUNS *

00:03.800 --> 00:05.324
* SAY, "DON'T MOVE,
STICK 'EM UP" *

00:06.400 --> 00:09.506
* YOU REALLY THINK
I'M GONNA RUN, RUN, RUN, RUN *

00:09.540 --> 00:10.632
* I'M NEVER GIVING UP

00:11.670 --> 00:14.605
* DON'T WANT TO, DON'T WANT TO

00:14.640 --> 00:17.370
* DON'T WANT TO MESS WITH ME

00:17.410 --> 00:20.618
* YOU DON'T WANT TO,
DON'T WANT TO *

00:20.650 --> 00:23.346
* DON'T WANT TO MESS WITH ME
OHH!

00:23.390 --> 00:26.814
OH!
* I GOT THE FEELING
I CAN BREAK *

00:26.860 --> 00:29.681
GIVE ME THE BALL.
ALL RIGHT, FIRST -- FIRST,
MCNALLY, WE'RE DRINKING.

00:29.730 --> 00:31.755
THIS ISN'T A DRINKING GAME,
AND THAT WAS MY POINT.
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT?

00:31.790 --> 00:33.348
LIFE IS A DRINKING GAME,
MCNALLY,

00:33.400 --> 00:35.356
AND YOU HAVE BEEN
PHONING IT IN.

00:35.400 --> 00:36.469
THERE. DOWN.

00:36.500 --> 00:39.367
DOWN THIS. DOWN IT NOW.
TO SAM SWAREK.
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:39.400 --> 00:41.368
* HERE THEY COMING WITH
THEIR GUNS, GUNS, GUNS, GUNS *
MNH, MNH-MNH.

00:41.400 --> 00:43.300
* SAY, "DON'T MOVE,
STICK 'EM UP" *
MNH-MNH!

00:43.340 --> 00:44.637
INSPECTOR.

00:44.670 --> 00:46.638
HI, HI.

00:46.680 --> 00:48.477
UH, YOU WANT TO PLAY?
THAT'S...

00:48.510 --> 00:49.738
NO. NO, NO.
BUT I NEED A WORD.

00:49.780 --> 00:52.112
ALL RIGHT, A WORD, A WORD.
THIS MAN NEEDS A WORD.

00:52.150 --> 00:53.640
SOMEBODY GET THIS MAN A WORD --
ANY WORD -- AND A DRINK.

00:53.680 --> 00:54.647
LET'S GET A DRINK.

00:54.680 --> 00:56.238
NO, THANKS.
MY CAR'S RUNNING.

00:56.290 --> 00:58.246
ALL RIGHT. EXCUSE ME.

00:58.290 --> 01:00.713
YOU, PECK...
TAKE MY SPANK HANDLE.

01:00.760 --> 01:02.489
[ LAUGHS ] OOH.
GO FORTH.

01:02.530 --> 01:06.091
I SHALL RETURN.
OOH, INSPECTOR, SORRY.

01:06.130 --> 01:08.257
I, UH, BURN ENERGY
WHEN I COMPETE.

01:08.300 --> 01:10.097
WELL, I'VE GOT A NEW SHIRT
FOR YOU.

01:10.130 --> 01:13.099
I'VE DECIDED ON
THE NEW STAFF SERGEANT.

01:13.140 --> 01:15.768
NO.
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

01:15.800 --> 01:18.564
YEAH, NO. I, UH --
I GOT TO TRAIN THAT ROOKIE.

01:18.610 --> 01:19.634
SOMEONE ELSE
CAN TRAIN HIM.

01:19.680 --> 01:22.774
JOHN...
I'M NOT A WHITE SHIRT.

01:22.810 --> 01:24.368
I'M A STREET COP.
I'M ONE OF THE BOYS.

01:24.410 --> 01:26.139
THAT'S SOMETHING
THAT I LOVE ABOUT MYSELF.

01:26.180 --> 01:28.671
EVERYBODY LIKES THAT ABOUT YOU.
THAT'S WHY YOU'RE MY GUY.

01:28.720 --> 01:30.142
THEY RESPECT YOU.

01:30.190 --> 01:32.511
YOU HAVING A GOOD TIME?
YEAH.

01:32.560 --> 01:35.120
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.
WELL...

01:35.160 --> 01:38.254
Man: OH. OH!

01:38.290 --> 01:40.793
* AND FIGHT UNTIL THE DEATH

01:40.830 --> 01:45.767
* 'CAUSE WHAT I STAND FOR
WILL NOT GIVE UP *
[ SIREN WAILING ]

01:45.800 --> 01:47.495
Psst!

01:48.800 --> 01:51.667
[ Laughing ] DON'T SHOOT.
IT'S JUST ME.

01:52.940 --> 01:56.546
GUESS WHAT.
WHAT?

01:56.580 --> 01:59.413
WE'RE GETTING A NEW
ACTING STAFF SERGEANT.
REALLY? WHO?

01:59.450 --> 02:00.917
IT'S GONNA BE OLIVER.
REALLY?

02:00.950 --> 02:02.713
I MEAN,
NOBODY KNOWS THAT, BUT --

02:02.750 --> 02:04.308
MM, CAN I HAVE
YOUR WATER?

02:04.350 --> 02:06.580
MM.
[ SLURPING ]

02:06.620 --> 02:09.453
OKAY,
AND ANOTHER THING --

02:09.490 --> 02:10.582
WE HAVE A NEW ROOKIE,

02:10.630 --> 02:13.190
AND OLIVER WAS SUPPOSED TO
TRAIN HIM, BUT NOW HE CAN'T.

02:13.230 --> 02:16.199
SO TONIGHT WAS JUST LIKE
ONE BIG MYSTERY

02:16.230 --> 02:17.595
WITH NO DETECTIVE THERE
TO SOLVE IT,

02:17.630 --> 02:19.336
WHICH, BY THE WAY, WHEN ARE YOU
COMING BACK TO WORK?

02:19.370 --> 02:21.930
WE SHOULD BREAK YOU OUT OF HERE,
MAN. YOU NEED TO BE FREE.

02:21.970 --> 02:24.234
I THINK YOU SHOULD DO IT.
GET YOU OUT OF HERE RIGHT NOW?
YEAH, MAN.

02:24.270 --> 02:26.170
NO, I THINK YOU SHOULD
TRAIN THE ROOKIE.

02:26.210 --> 02:27.472
OH, YEAH, GREAT IDEA.
YOU'D BE GREAT.

02:27.510 --> 02:28.534
MM-HMM. FOR SURE.
I'M DRUNK.

02:28.580 --> 02:29.604
WELL, YOU WON'T BE DRUNK
TOMORROW.

02:29.650 --> 02:31.868
[ SIGHS ]
[ MONITOR BEEPS ]

02:31.910 --> 02:33.946
I WOULD BE REALLY GOOD AT IT,
ACTUALLY.

02:33.980 --> 02:37.279
YEAH.
PROBABLY THE BEST.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:37.320 --> 02:38.912
YOUR FEET ARE FREEZING.

02:38.950 --> 02:41.259
NO, THEY'RE SWEATY.
I'VE BEEN COMPETING ALL NIGHT.

02:42.560 --> 02:43.788
I'M INTERRUPTING.
SORRY.

02:43.830 --> 02:44.922
NO, NO, NO, NO.
THAT'S OKAY.

02:44.960 --> 02:47.258
I WAS JUST, UH,
YOU KNOW, POPPING BY.

02:47.300 --> 02:49.427
NO. WHAT?
YOU DON'T HAVE TO...
SO, GOOD NIGHT.

02:49.470 --> 02:50.698
DON'T LET
THE BEDBUGS BITE.

02:50.730 --> 02:52.561
SAY A PRAYER, YOU KNOW,
AND ALL THAT GOOD STUFF.

02:52.600 --> 02:54.568
SAM DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT A PRAYER IS.

02:54.600 --> 02:56.363
WHAT DO YOU MEAN? I'VE SAID
SOME PRAYERS IN MY DAY.

02:56.410 --> 02:57.399
[ Chuckling ]
YEAH, RIGHT.

02:57.440 --> 02:59.305
OKAY,
SO, I'M GONNA GO.

02:59.340 --> 03:01.900
OKAY, WELL, I GUESS
I SHOULD SAY GOODBYE NOW, THEN,

03:01.940 --> 03:04.249
'CAUSE, UH,
I GOT TO HEAD OUT TOMORROW.

03:04.280 --> 03:06.919
OH, OKAY, WELL, I MEAN,
I CAN GIVE YOU A RIDE.

03:06.950 --> 03:08.872
YEAH?
[ Laughing ] NO.

03:08.920 --> 03:11.241
I DON'T HAVE A CAR.
YOU CAN TAKE MY TRUCK.

03:11.290 --> 03:12.518
OKAY.
OKAY?

03:12.560 --> 03:14.812
THAT WOULD BE GREAT,
SERIOUSLY.

03:14.860 --> 03:17.556
MY TRAIN LEAVES AT 8:00.
OKAY.

03:17.590 --> 03:19.649
SEE YOU TOMORROW, HMM?
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

03:19.700 --> 03:21.691
BYE.

03:23.930 --> 03:26.398
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

03:27.700 --> 03:29.304
WHAT?

03:29.340 --> 03:30.705
[ SIREN WAILING ]

03:33.740 --> 03:35.708
HEY.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

03:35.740 --> 03:37.549
UH, I...
I JUST DROPPED MY GO-BAG.

03:37.580 --> 03:39.411
A LOT OF GO IN YOUR BAG.
[ SLURPS ]

03:39.450 --> 03:41.315
ARE YOU HITTING ON ME?

03:41.350 --> 03:43.784
YOU'RE THE NEW ROOKIE.

03:43.820 --> 03:46.653
YEAH, HOW DID YOU KNOW?
DETECTIVE, RIGHT?

03:46.690 --> 03:47.918
NOT QUITE.

03:47.960 --> 03:51.282
[ DOOR BUZZES ]
WELCOME TO 15.

03:54.060 --> 03:57.518
WHOO! WHOO!
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

03:57.570 --> 04:00.630
AW, PUT IT IN A CAGE, PECK.
COME ON, BUDDY.

04:00.670 --> 04:03.036
YEP. YEAH, THANK YOU.
THANK YOU.

04:03.070 --> 04:06.506
YES, I FEEL VERY SPECIAL.
IT'S A WONDERFUL DAY.

04:06.540 --> 04:09.509
UH, I WOULD LIKE TO INTRODUCE
OUR NEWEST RECRUIT HERE AT 15.

04:09.550 --> 04:10.608
THIS IS DUNCAN MOORE.

04:10.650 --> 04:12.447
[ APPLAUSE ]

04:13.850 --> 04:14.839
THERE YOU GO. GREAT.

04:14.880 --> 04:16.689
OKAY, SO, YOU'RE PART
OF THE FAMILY NOW, ROOKIE.

04:16.720 --> 04:17.914
I'M SURE YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS.

04:17.950 --> 04:21.351
MM. NO.
NO?
WE DO NOT HAVE TO LIKE YOU.

04:21.390 --> 04:22.948
WE DON'T HAVE TO BE NICE
TO YOU.

04:22.990 --> 04:25.629
AND WE CAN MAKE FUN OF YOU
WHENEVER WE WANT BECAUSE,

04:25.660 --> 04:27.890
WHEN IT REALLY COMES DOWN TO IT,
WE'LL ALWAYS HAVE YOUR BACK.

04:27.930 --> 04:30.728
OH.
AND I HAVE YOURS...SIR.

04:30.770 --> 04:32.431
ALL RIGHT.

04:32.470 --> 04:36.839
UH, OKAY, SO, UM...
FIRST DAY OF A NEW ROTATION.

04:36.870 --> 04:40.829
YOU, UH, SEE WHO -- YOUR
ASSIGNMENTS ARE UP ON THE BOARD,

04:40.880 --> 04:44.668
AND THAT'S WHO YOU'LL BE
RIDING WITH FOR THE DAY.

04:44.710 --> 04:48.373
UH, OKAY, THAT'S IT.
YOU'RE DISMISSED.

04:48.420 --> 04:49.648
OFF YOU GO. BE GOOD COPS.
COME HERE, MOORE.

04:49.690 --> 04:51.942
[ COUGHS ]

04:51.990 --> 04:54.083
[ BEEPING ]

04:54.120 --> 04:56.953
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

04:56.990 --> 04:58.821
Andy: OLIVER.
YES.

04:58.860 --> 05:00.896
SORRY.
STAFF SERGEANT SHAW.
YEAH?

05:00.930 --> 05:03.069
[ SIGHS ]
I CAN DO IT.

05:03.100 --> 05:05.694
DO WHAT?
TRAIN THE ROOKIE, SIR.

05:05.730 --> 05:07.891
I DON'T THINK THAT'S
A GOOD IDEA, MCNALLY.

05:07.940 --> 05:09.908
I CAN DO IT, OKAY?
I THOUGHT LONG AND HARD ABOUT IT

05:09.940 --> 05:11.805
LAST NIGHT WHEN I WAS --
WHEN I COULDN'T SLEEP.

05:11.840 --> 05:13.376
IT'S A BIG RESPONSIBILITY
TO TRAIN A COP.

05:13.410 --> 05:14.809
I DON'T WANT TO TRAIN
A COP.

05:14.840 --> 05:16.398
I WANT TO TRAIN
A SUPER COP.

05:16.450 --> 05:17.803
SOLD.

05:17.850 --> 05:19.477
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM, SHAW?

05:21.980 --> 05:24.540
SHE'S GREAT. I TRAINED HER.
SURE.

05:24.590 --> 05:27.559
THAT SE'I'I'LES IT, THEN.
GREAT.

05:27.590 --> 05:30.320
COME ON, ROOKIE.
GRAB YOUR GO-BAG. LET'S ROCK.

05:31.860 --> 05:34.556
GET ME MCNALLY'S
PERSONNEL FILE.
YEAH.

05:34.600 --> 05:37.694
[ SIREN WAILS ]

05:37.730 --> 05:40.563
THIS IS A BIG MOMENT --

05:40.600 --> 05:42.807
FIRST TIME HEADING
TO THE SQUAD CAR.
YEP.

05:42.840 --> 05:44.432
DO YOU MIND?

05:44.470 --> 05:46.631
UH, NOPE.
THANK YOU.

05:51.010 --> 05:52.443
MM.

05:52.480 --> 05:55.415
HEY, YOU KNOW,
I'M -- I'M REALLY HAPPY

05:55.450 --> 05:57.918
THAT I'M BEING TAUGHT
BY A WOMAN.

05:57.950 --> 05:59.679
YOU KNOW?

05:59.720 --> 06:01.711
I-I JUST FEEL LIKE
I COULD BE MORE MYSELF,

06:01.760 --> 06:03.728
LIKE I DON'T --
I DON'T HAVE TO PRETEND TO --

06:03.760 --> 06:07.457
TO BE ALL MACHO AND --
AND ACT LIKE MINI NOT NERVOUS.

06:07.500 --> 06:08.398
[ POLICE RADIO CHA'I'I'ER ]

06:08.430 --> 06:11.593
AND THIS IS MY FIRST DAY,
TOO, AS A T.O.

06:11.630 --> 06:14.463
ARE -- ARE YOU NERVOUS?
YEAH, A BIT.

06:14.500 --> 06:15.990
I MEAN, I FEEL LIKE I HAVE
SO MUCH TO TELL YOU,

06:16.040 --> 06:18.099
BUT I DON'T WANT TO BOMBARD YOU
WITH INFORMATION.

06:18.140 --> 06:20.574
OH, NO, BOMBARD ME.
BOMBARD ME.

06:20.610 --> 06:22.100
HEY, ARE YOU INTO
SELF-FEEDBACK?

06:22.140 --> 06:24.108
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT THAT IS.

06:24.150 --> 06:25.970
OKAY, WELL, THAT'S -- THAT'S
SOMETHING THAT WE PRACT ICED

06:26.010 --> 06:28.570
IN ONE OF OUR SEMINAR COURSES
AT COLLEGE, WHERE --

06:28.620 --> 06:31.714
SURPRISE, SURPRISE --
THE PROF WAS A WOMAN.

06:31.750 --> 06:33.456
BUT IT'S PRETI'Y
SELF-EXPLANATORY.

06:33.490 --> 06:35.117
UM, EACH PARTICIPANT
PROVIDES,

06:35.160 --> 06:37.822
UH, FEEDBACK
ON THEIR OWN PERFORMANCE.

06:37.860 --> 06:41.819
SO, INSTEAD OF, YOU KNOW,
YOU "GRADING" ME,

06:41.860 --> 06:45.091
I TELL YOU HOW I'VE DONE, AND --
AND -- AND HOW YOU'VE DONE.

06:45.130 --> 06:46.961
AND YOU -- YOU'D DO THE SAME,
OF COURSE.

06:47.000 --> 06:47.796
OH, OKAY.

06:47.840 --> 06:51.708
WELL, HERE, UM,
THERE'S PROTOCOL,

06:51.740 --> 06:53.469
AND I JUST WRITE THE REPORT
MYSELF.

06:53.510 --> 06:57.048
RIGHT, RIGHT.
MESSAGE RECEIVED.

06:57.080 --> 07:00.641
YEAH, BUT YOU CAN BET THAT RULE
WAS MADE BY A MAN.

07:00.680 --> 07:02.648
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

07:02.690 --> 07:03.486
Steve: GOOD MORNING.

07:03.520 --> 07:07.115
TODAY HAS TO BE
AN EIGHT-HOUR DAY.

07:07.160 --> 07:09.583
OKAY.
BUT I GOT TO CATALOG
ALL OF THIS.

07:09.630 --> 07:12.451
PLUS, I HAVE TO TAKE STATEMENTS
FROM TWO WITNESSES

07:12.500 --> 07:13.990
ON THE KRIZANC CASE,
EVEN THOUGH THEY'RE FULL OF IT,

07:14.030 --> 07:15.224
'CAUSE WE ALL KNOW
JOEY NELSON DID IT.

07:15.260 --> 07:16.864
I CAN FILE THAT STUFF FOR YOU,
IF YOU WANT.

07:16.900 --> 07:18.959
WHAT? GUNS AND GANGS
NOT KEEPING YOU BUSY?

07:19.000 --> 07:21.696
THAT'S ONE OF THE DOWNSIDES
OF BEING SO GOOD --

07:21.740 --> 07:23.469
I'M ON TOP
OF MY PAPERWORK.

07:23.510 --> 07:24.761
50 NOW I GOT NOTHING TO DO

07:24.810 --> 07:26.971
BUT DRINK COFFEE
AND CHECK OUT THE LADIES.

07:27.010 --> 07:29.979
NOW, I CAN HANDLE
A HUMBLE BRAG

07:30.010 --> 07:32.478
IF IT MEANS YOU WILL TAKE
ALL THIS OFF MY PLATE FOR ME.

07:32.520 --> 07:34.078
YEAH, NO PROBLEM.

07:34.120 --> 07:35.815
I OWE YOU.

07:35.850 --> 07:37.215
EIGHT-HOUR DAY.
EIGHT-HOUR DAY.

07:37.250 --> 07:39.081
IF I KEEP SAYING IT,
IT'LL HAPPEN, RIGHT?

07:39.120 --> 07:40.815
I THINK I CAN. I THINK I CAN.
I THINK I CAN.

07:40.860 --> 07:42.213
OKAY,
YOU'RE GONNA OBSERVE ME.

07:42.260 --> 07:44.182
I WANT YOU TO LISTEN
TO WHAT I'M GONNA SAY,

07:44.230 --> 07:46.152
AND YOU'RE GONNA DO
WHAT I TELL YOU TO DO.

07:46.190 --> 07:48.158
[ CLICKING ]

07:48.200 --> 07:50.521
WHAT -- WHAT --
WHAT IS HAPPENING RIGHT NOW?

07:50.570 --> 07:52.936
OH, SORRY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:52.970 --> 07:55.939
UM, I'M -- I'M JUST -- I'M JUST
SENDING MY BOY THE SHOT.

07:55.970 --> 07:58.530
ME IN A UNIFORM.
YEAH, OKAY, POP QUIZ, OKAY?

07:58.570 --> 07:59.468
TRAFFIC STOP.

07:59.510 --> 08:00.875
WHAT IS THE FIRST THING
YOU'RE GONNA DO

08:00.910 --> 08:02.036
BEFORE YOU APPROACH
THAT CAR?

08:02.080 --> 08:04.947
UH, DO A QUICK SCAN,
AND THEN, UH, SEE IF THE --
WRONG.

08:04.980 --> 08:06.675
CALL ME.

08:06.720 --> 08:09.814
UH, A MAN PULLS A KNIFE.
I SHOOT HIM.

08:09.850 --> 08:11.511
YOU'RE JUST GONNA SHOOT HIM?
YOU'RE NOT -- YOU'RE NOT GONNA

08:11.550 --> 08:12.949
TALK TO HIM AND TRY TO GET HIM
TO DROP THE WEAPON FIRST?

08:12.990 --> 08:14.855
ABSOLUTELY.
OH, OKAY.
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA SAY?

08:14.890 --> 08:16.755
PUT YOUR HANDS UP
BEFORE I SHOOT YOU!

08:16.790 --> 08:19.258
NEVER MIND.
JUST CALL ME, ALL RIGHT?

08:19.290 --> 08:21.997
OKAY.
IF THERE'S A ROBBERY,
CALL ME.

08:22.030 --> 08:24.260
YOU SEE A DRUG DEAL GO DOWN,
YOU'RE GONNA CALL ME.

08:24.300 --> 08:27.861
YOU SEE A KID FALL OFF
A TRICYCLE, CALL ME.

08:27.900 --> 08:30.004
I AM YOUR TRAINING OFFICER,
OKAY?

08:30.040 --> 08:32.133
SO, NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,
YOU'RE GONNA DO WHAT?

08:32.170 --> 08:33.273
ASSESS THE SITUATION --

08:33.310 --> 08:35.972
OH, MY GOD. CALL ME.

08:36.010 --> 08:37.978
RIGHT. GOTCHA.

08:38.010 --> 08:40.149
I JUST -- I THOUGHT
IT WAS A TRICK QUESTION.

08:42.180 --> 08:44.614
DISPATCHER: 1504, we've got
a possible break-and-enter

08:44.650 --> 08:47.289
at Pawn Kings, 2793 Gerrard.

08:47.320 --> 08:50.619
Uh, the door's open and
there's broken glass inside.

08:50.660 --> 08:52.082
WELL,
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

08:54.130 --> 08:56.223
CALL YOU?
ANSWER THE RADIO.

08:56.260 --> 08:57.261
RIGHT.

09:01.900 --> 09:04.630
PAWN KINGS, HERE WE GO.

09:07.080 --> 09:09.298
HEY, WAIT!

09:09.340 --> 09:11.547
[ POLICE RADIO CHA'I'I'ER ]

09:21.220 --> 09:24.758
WHOA, YOU ALWAYS
STAY BEHIND ME.

09:24.790 --> 09:27.623
[ POLICE RADIO CHA'I'I'ER ]
OKAY.

09:27.660 --> 09:29.218
THAT LOOKS LIKE
A DEAD DUDE'S LEGS.

09:29.260 --> 09:32.866
SIR?

09:32.900 --> 09:34.595
YEAH.
SIR, YOU GOT TO WAKE UP.

09:34.640 --> 09:36.733
OHH.
HI.

09:36.770 --> 09:38.931
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN HERE?

09:38.970 --> 09:43.077
UM, RIGHT.
UH, LAST NIGHT, UH...

09:45.380 --> 09:47.211
UH...

09:47.250 --> 09:50.083
LIFE PRESENTS A GIFT.

09:50.120 --> 09:52.179
TAKE THE GIFT
AND BE GRATEFUL.

09:52.220 --> 09:54.381
GIFTS WILL COME AGAIN.

09:54.420 --> 09:57.628
THE DOOR WAS OPEN.
IT WAS COLD OUT.

09:57.660 --> 09:58.786
COME ON.
LET'S GET YOU UP.

09:58.830 --> 10:01.196
OKAY.

10:01.230 --> 10:03.198
ANYBODY ELSE IN HERE?
NOPE.

10:03.230 --> 10:04.299
DID YOU TAKE ANYTHING?

10:04.330 --> 10:06.867
FEEL FREE TO SEARCH ME.

10:06.900 --> 10:10.404
I DON'T THINK THERE'S ANYTHING,
BUT I DRINK TOO MUCH.

10:10.440 --> 10:13.375
A HAIKU MAN.
I LIKE HAIKU.

10:13.410 --> 10:15.970
I'M GONNA NEED YOUR FULL NAME
AND ADDRESS.

10:16.010 --> 10:18.069
MY NAME'S YOSA BUSON.

10:18.110 --> 10:20.340
ANY I.D. ON YOU?
I DON'T.

10:20.380 --> 10:23.816
B-U-S-O-N.

10:23.850 --> 10:25.943
DON'T HAVE AN ADDRESS.

10:25.990 --> 10:30.780
I USE THE SHELTER
ON HALLIDAY.

10:30.830 --> 10:34.926
CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A MINUTE?
EXCUSE ME.

10:34.960 --> 10:39.067
UM, EVEN IF HE DIDN'T BREAK IN,
IT'S STILL ILLEGAL ENTRY.

10:39.100 --> 10:40.988
YOU'RE LOOKING
FOR A MYSTERY,

10:41.040 --> 10:44.009
BUT THERE'S NONE.

10:44.040 --> 10:46.736
LOOK, HE'S HARMLESS, OKAY?
HE CAME IN FROM THE COLD.

10:46.780 --> 10:48.873
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

10:48.910 --> 10:50.775
OFFICER MOORE IS
GONNA SEARCH YOU.

10:50.810 --> 10:53.119
IF HE DOESN'T FIND ANYTHING,
YOU'RE FREE TO GO.

10:53.150 --> 10:55.414
I WANT YOU TO SEE
IF YOU CAN TRACK DOWN THE OWNER.

10:55.450 --> 10:58.044
I'M GONNA CLEAR
THE REST OF THE BUILDING.
MM-HMM.

10:58.090 --> 10:59.910
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

10:59.960 --> 11:02.281
CAN YOU PLEASE
PUT YOUR ARMS UP?

11:02.320 --> 11:05.756
