22:59.570 --> 23:01.834
YEAH, SOMEBODY BY THE NAME
OF DUNCAN MOORE.

23:01.880 --> 23:04.178
HIS PAWS
WERE ALL OVER IT,

23:04.210 --> 23:07.509
SO IF OUR GUY'S PRINTS
WERE ON IT ANYWHERE,

23:07.550 --> 23:09.768
THEY CAN'T BE FOUND NOW.

23:09.820 --> 23:12.914
NOW THIS CASE IS GONNA TAKE
DAYS, WEEKS, MONTHS.

23:12.950 --> 23:14.451
TRACE, I'M SORRY.

23:14.490 --> 23:16.856
[ SIGHS ]

23:22.030 --> 23:23.691
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT HE WAS GONNA
CONTAMINATE THE SCENE.

23:23.730 --> 23:24.992
I JUST GOT OFF THE PHONE
WITH THE VICTIM'S WIFE,

23:25.030 --> 23:25.962
AND SHE IS GONNA LODGE
A COMPLAINT

23:26.000 --> 23:29.436
ABOUT YOUR TRIP TO HER HOUSE
THIS AFTERNOON.

23:29.470 --> 23:33.429
AND MAYBE RIGHTLY SO, OKAY?
SHE WANTS AN APOLOGY.

23:33.480 --> 23:35.436
WHAT HAPPENED?

23:35.480 --> 23:37.573
HE'S NEW.

23:37.610 --> 23:39.441
HE'S YOUR ROOKIE.
WELL, HE'S LEARNING.

23:39.480 --> 23:40.947
HE'S YOUR ROOKIE.

23:40.980 --> 23:43.210
OKAY.

23:43.250 --> 23:44.842
[ SIGHS ]
THAT'S MY FAULT.

23:44.890 --> 23:46.846
I TRI-- I TRIED TO TELL YOU,
MAN. YOU KNOW?

23:46.890 --> 23:48.118
"I WANT TO LEAVE HIM
ON A DESK.

23:48.160 --> 23:49.912
I WANT TO FEEL HIM OUT, SEE
WHO'S RIGHT TO TRAIN THIS KID,"

23:49.960 --> 23:52.053
BUT YOU JUMPED IN.
I KNOW.

23:52.090 --> 23:53.591
IS THAT HOW
YOU'RE TRAINING HIM?

23:53.630 --> 23:55.450
NO,
I TOLD HIM TO CALL ME.

23:55.500 --> 23:59.129
HE'S NOT TO CALL YOU --
HE'S TO STAND RIGHT BESIDE YOU.

23:59.170 --> 24:00.592
[ COUGHS ] OKAY.

24:00.640 --> 24:02.858
UM, YOU EVER HEARD THAT --
THAT SAYING,

24:02.900 --> 24:04.208
"SLOW DOWN,
WE'RE IN A HURRY"?

24:05.940 --> 24:08.909
OKAY, WHEN YOU WERE A ROOK,
WE'D ROLL UP TO A HOT CALL,

24:08.940 --> 24:10.703
REMEMBER, I'D --
I'D TAKE A SHOT OF COFFEE,

24:10.750 --> 24:11.899
OR I'D PULL OUT A SANDWICH
AND HAVE A BITE?

24:11.950 --> 24:14.714
MM-HMM.
THAT WAS JUST TO GIVE YOU
A MOMENT TO BREATHE.

24:14.750 --> 24:16.718
YOU KNOW, GIVE YOU JUST A SECOND
TO COLLECT YOURSELF

24:16.750 --> 24:17.682
BEFORE WE WENT IN.

24:17.720 --> 24:20.985
YOU KNOW, ANDY,
THIS IS -- THIS IS DOMINOES.

24:21.020 --> 24:22.851
HE FAILS, YOU FAIL.

24:22.890 --> 24:26.121
IF YOU FAIL, I FAIL, AND H
CAN'T FAIL, NOT WITH THIS KID.

24:26.160 --> 24:28.526
WHY NOT WITH THIS KID?

24:28.560 --> 24:31.791
MOORE IS
HIS MOTHER'S NAME.

24:31.830 --> 24:33.661
HIS STEPFATHER
IS ALONSO SANTANA.

24:33.700 --> 24:37.261
WHOA, WHY WOULDN'T YOU
TELL ME THAT?

24:37.300 --> 24:39.165
UH, I AM TELLING YOU NOW.
WELL, NOW WHAT
AM I SUPPOSED TO DO?

24:39.210 --> 24:40.734
YOU KEEP HIM
ON A SHORT LEASH.

24:40.780 --> 24:44.170
YOU JUST FIGURE IT OUT.
YOU DO IT.
OHH.

24:46.150 --> 24:49.847
LOOK, I HAD NO IDEA
THAT THE GOLF CLUB WAS EVIDENCE.

24:49.880 --> 24:52.280
THAT'S THE POINT.
WHY DID YOU PICK IT UP?

24:52.320 --> 24:54.788
I GOLF.
THAT'S WHAT GOLFERS DO.

24:54.820 --> 24:57.050
WELL,
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME

24:57.090 --> 24:59.627
THAT YOUR STEPFATH ER
IS THE COMMISSIONER, HMM?

24:59.660 --> 25:03.596
WHAT WOULD THAT CHANGE
IF I TOLD YOU THAT?

25:03.630 --> 25:04.927
THAT'S NOT THE POINT --
YOU SHOULD HAVE TOLD ME.

25:04.970 --> 25:06.926
OKAY, WELL, I THINK
IT'D BE UNPROFESSIONAL FOR ME

25:06.970 --> 25:09.530
TO JUST THROW HIS NAME AROUND
AND -- AND -- AND ACT LIKE

25:09.570 --> 25:11.765
I SHOULD GET SPECIAL TREATMENT,
OKAY? IT'S IRRELEVANT.

25:11.810 --> 25:13.129
IT'S NOT.

25:13.170 --> 25:16.139
LOOK, I'M SORRY TO DISAGREE
WITH YOU, BUT I THINK IT IS.

25:16.180 --> 25:17.738
OKAY?
I'M HERE ON MY OWN MERIT,

25:17.780 --> 25:19.645
AND HE'S NOT EVEN
MY REAL FATHER, ANYWAY.

25:19.680 --> 25:21.910
[ ALARM CHIRPS ]
LOOK, I'M SORRY, OKAY?

25:21.950 --> 25:24.009
I SHOULDN'T HAVE TOUCHED
THE GOLF CLUB.

25:24.050 --> 25:25.608
YOU'RE RIGHT TO GET ON ME
ABOUT IT.

25:25.650 --> 25:26.878
[ SIREN WAILS ]

25:26.920 --> 25:28.854
WHERE --
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

25:28.890 --> 25:31.085
WE'RE GOING TO APOLOGIZE
TO THE VICTIM'S WIFE. GET IN.

25:33.900 --> 25:36.994
LOOKS LIKE THE ONLY THING
HAWKED 26 DAYS AGO AT PAWN KINGS

25:37.030 --> 25:40.591
WERE MUSICAL INSTRUMENTS --
FRENCH HORNS, VIOLINS.

25:40.640 --> 25:41.993
WHAT -- DID THE SYMPHONY
GO BANKRUPT?

25:42.040 --> 25:43.905
YOU KNOW,
I THINK I GOT SOMETHING.

25:43.940 --> 25:47.262
AN ANTIQUE HOCKEY RING PAWNED
BY A RAY SPENCER --

25:47.310 --> 25:49.278
1139 CRESCENT ROAD.

25:49.310 --> 25:50.299
[ Muffled ] RAY SPENCER.

25:50.340 --> 25:52.308
[ CRUNCHING ]

25:52.350 --> 25:54.671
YOU KNOW, I-I WOULDN'T
EAT THOSE, IF I WAS YOU.

25:54.720 --> 25:56.039
WHY?
WERE THEY IN THE TOILET?

25:56.080 --> 25:57.581
NO.

25:57.620 --> 25:59.679
THEN I DON'T REALLY CARE.
I'M HUNGRY.

25:59.720 --> 26:01.017
PROBABLY SPRINKLED
WITH ROOFI ES.

26:01.060 --> 26:03.881
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]
ALL RIGHT,
HE'S GOT A RECORD --

26:03.930 --> 26:05.249
POSSESSION
OF STOLEN PROPERTY,

26:05.290 --> 26:07.349
STILL LIVES
WITH HIS PARENTS.

26:07.390 --> 26:08.823
HEY, BILL POWER
IS STILL SELLING THAT RING.

26:08.860 --> 26:10.225
WAS.
NO, "IS."

26:10.260 --> 26:11.898
IT'S POSTED UP
ON THE VICTIM'S PROFILE.

26:11.930 --> 26:13.989
STARTING BID AT $10,000.

26:14.040 --> 26:17.601
AUCTION DOESN'T CLOSE
ANOTHER TWO DAYS.

26:19.640 --> 26:21.779
[ SIGHS ]

26:21.810 --> 26:24.301
YOU KNOW WHAT, BOSS?

26:24.350 --> 26:25.908
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

26:25.950 --> 26:29.374
IT'S MY SCREW-UP.
NEEDS TO BE MY APOLOGY.

26:29.420 --> 26:30.887
WELL, I HAVE TO GO IN THERE
WITH YOU.

26:30.920 --> 26:33.286
BUT I'LL ONLY BE CONCERNED
WITH IMPRESSING YOU, OKAY?

26:33.320 --> 26:36.016
IT'S NOT
EASY SAYING SORRY,

26:36.060 --> 26:37.618
ESPECIALLY IN FRONT
OF AN AUDIENCE.

26:37.660 --> 26:39.252
GIVE ME ANOTHER CHANCE.

26:39.290 --> 26:43.124
YOU NEED TO MAKE IT
SHORT AND SWEET.

26:43.160 --> 26:46.823
I WANT YOU TO GO IN THERE
AND APOLOGIZE SINCERELY,

26:46.870 --> 26:47.996
THEN GET
RIGHT BACK OUT HERE.

26:48.040 --> 26:50.736
OKAY.

26:50.770 --> 26:52.761
[ SEAT BELT CLICKS ]

26:58.080 --> 27:01.015
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

27:07.190 --> 27:10.057
[ KNOCKING ON DOOR ]

27:18.430 --> 27:20.864
[ DOOR CREAKS ]

27:20.900 --> 27:22.868
HELLO?

27:22.900 --> 27:24.731
[ DOG BARKS IN DISTANCE ]

27:24.770 --> 27:28.035
IT'S OFFICER MOORE.
CAN I COME IN?

27:31.210 --> 27:33.178
I'M -- I'M COMING IN.

27:33.210 --> 27:35.440
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

27:35.480 --> 27:38.643
MRS. POWER, IT'S OFFICER MOORE.
I WAS HERE EARLIER TODAY.

27:41.160 --> 27:42.388
HEY.

27:42.420 --> 27:45.321
UH, WHO ARE YOU?
I'M RAY.

27:45.360 --> 27:49.057
OH. IS, UM,
MRS. POWER AROUND?

27:49.100 --> 27:52.866
MM. [ CLEARS THROAT ]
NO, SHE'S OUT.

27:52.900 --> 27:56.734
UM. SORRY. I JUST LET MYSELF IN.
THE DOOR WAS OPEN.

27:56.770 --> 27:58.738
ARE YOU A RELATIVE
OR SOMETHING?

27:58.770 --> 28:01.034
UH [CLEARS THROAT]
I'M A FRIEND.

28:01.080 --> 28:02.274
OH.

28:02.310 --> 28:04.744
UM, YEAH, I JUST
REALLY NEED TO TALK TO HER.

28:04.780 --> 28:06.748
YOU KNOW,
I FEEL REALLY BAD.

28:06.780 --> 28:08.179
CAME HERE EARLIER
TO LET HER KNOW

28:08.220 --> 28:10.814
THAT HER HUSBAND HAD PASSED
AWAY, AND, AH, I SCREWED IT UP.

28:10.850 --> 28:11.942
WHO DIED?

28:11.990 --> 28:14.959
HER HUSBAND, UH,
DOWN AT THE PAWN SHOP.

28:14.990 --> 28:17.754
I'M -- I'M -- I'M REALLY SORRY
IF YOU WERE CLOSE.

28:17.790 --> 28:19.382
NO, HE DIDN'T DIE.

28:19.430 --> 28:22.399
NO, NO. HE DID.

28:22.430 --> 28:24.728
UM, I'M SORRY.

28:24.770 --> 28:26.795
UH, CAN YOU TELL ME -- WHAT --
WHAT IS YOUR NAME AGAIN?

28:32.340 --> 28:35.036
LOOK, I'M JUST LOOKING
FOR MY RING, OKAY?

28:35.080 --> 28:37.435
I WENT TO THE STORE, AND I TRIED
TO BUY THE THING BACK,

28:37.480 --> 28:39.175
AND THE GUY WOULDN'T EVEN
GIVE IT BACK TO ME, OKAY?

28:39.210 --> 28:41.314
OKAY.

28:41.350 --> 28:42.908
I'M -- NOW I'M STARTING
TO PUT THIS TOGETHER.

28:42.950 --> 28:45.111
NOW, YOU -- YOU WERE THE GUY
THAT BROKE INTO THE PAWNSHOP.

28:45.150 --> 28:47.448
I REALLY NEED
THAT RING BACK.

28:47.490 --> 28:49.788
YEAH, OKAY,
JUST DO ME A FAVOR --

28:49.820 --> 28:51.424
CAN YOU JUST TURN AROUND AND
PUT YOUR HANDS BEHIND YOUR BACK?

28:51.460 --> 28:53.087
I REALLY NEED
THAT RING BACK.
NO, I GET THAT.

28:53.130 --> 28:54.825
JUST TURN AROUND AND PUT
YOUR HANDS BEHIND YOUR BACK.

28:54.860 --> 28:57.226
IT'S FINE, OKAY? THAT'S
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO. OKAY?

28:57.260 --> 28:59.091
ALL RIGHT, JUST PUT THEM BOTH
BEHIND YOUR BACK, OKAY?

28:59.130 --> 29:02.031
I-I WAS-- I WASN'T EVEN --
YEAH, JUST TURN AROUND.

29:02.070 --> 29:04.038
TURN AROUND. TURN AROUND.
I WASN'T EVEN THERE
T-TRYING TO ROB THE PLACE.

29:04.070 --> 29:05.298
YEAH.
OKAY?

29:05.340 --> 29:06.364
WE'LL FIND THE RING.
DON'T WORRY.

29:06.410 --> 29:07.434
CAN YOU PUT THAT HAND
BEHIND YOUR BACK, PLEASE?

29:07.470 --> 29:09.131
[ HANDCUFFS CLICK ]
WE'LL FIND THE RING, YOU KNOW,

29:09.180 --> 29:11.068
BUT YOU DID KILL THE GUY,
YOU KNOW?

29:11.110 --> 29:12.441
COME ON!
NO, BUT, HEY, LISTEN.
PLEASE LISTEN TO ME, MAN.

29:12.480 --> 29:13.913
OKAY, FIRST OF ALL, TURN AROUND.
NO. LISTEN TO ME.

29:13.950 --> 29:15.349
TURN AROUND.
PUT YOUR HANDS BEHIND YOUR BACK.

29:15.380 --> 29:16.472
JUST SHUT UP!
TURN AROUND RIGHT NOW!

29:16.520 --> 29:17.839
NO!
NO, NO, TURN --

29:17.890 --> 29:19.039
PUT THAT DOWN!
PUT THE SWORD DOWN.

29:19.090 --> 29:21.058
I DID NOT -- OKAY, LISTEN.
PUT THE SWORD DOWN
RIGHT NOW.

29:21.090 --> 29:22.785
Ray: OKAY, QUIET.
JUST PUT THE SWORD DOWN
RIGHT NOW.

29:22.820 --> 29:24.253
I DIDN'T KILL ANYBODY,
ALL RIGHT?
JUST PUT IT DOWN!

29:24.290 --> 29:27.384
DISPATCHER:
All units, we have a BOLO
on a Ray Spencer, 30 years old,

29:27.430 --> 29:29.398
Wanted in connection
with a homicide

29:29.430 --> 29:32.069
this morning at Pawn Kings,
driving a red Sunfire

29:32.100 --> 29:35.888
Alfa-Zulu-Uniform-
Whiskey-3-9-5.

29:35.940 --> 29:37.908
THIS IS 1504.

29:37.940 --> 29:41.273
HE'S AT 1544 CONLEY STREET.
SEND BACKUP RIGHT AWAY.

29:49.520 --> 29:51.442
PLEASE LISTEN TO ME!
PUT THE SWORD
ON THE DAMN GROUND!

29:51.490 --> 29:53.378
PUT IT DOWN!
PUT THE SWORD DOWN!
I JUST WANT MY DAD'S RING!

29:53.420 --> 29:54.978
DUNCAN,
I'M RIGHT BEHIND YOU!

29:55.020 --> 29:56.510
PUT THE SWORD ON THE GROUND
RIGHT NOW!

29:56.560 --> 29:57.584
HOLSTER YOUR WEAPON, NOW.

29:57.620 --> 30:00.225
NO, NOT UNTIL HE DROPS IT.
PUT THE GUN AWAY NOW!

30:05.300 --> 30:06.858
YOU RAY SPENCER?

30:06.900 --> 30:08.231
YEAH.
HE'S A KILLER.

30:08.270 --> 30:09.498
HE KILLED MR. POWERS.
I DIDN'T KILL ANYBODY!

30:09.540 --> 30:10.598
YES, YOU DID!
STOP. STOP.

30:10.640 --> 30:13.973
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

30:17.380 --> 30:19.075
YOU WANT SOME GUM?

30:19.110 --> 30:20.839
NO.

30:24.020 --> 30:26.238
WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON, RAY?

30:26.290 --> 30:30.112
I WAS LOOKING
FOR MY DAD'S HOCKEY RING.

30:30.160 --> 30:32.128
I PAWNED IT, OKAY?

30:32.160 --> 30:34.549
IT WASN'T AT THE STORE,
SO IT'S GOT TO BE HERE, RIGHT?

30:34.600 --> 30:35.555
GO LOOK FOR THE RING.

30:35.600 --> 30:37.352
I DON'T KNOW WHERE IT IS.
LOOK AT THIS MESS.

30:37.400 --> 30:38.958
LOOK AROUND.
LOOK,
WE NEED TO TAKE HIM IN.

30:39.000 --> 30:40.092
WE NEED TO BOOK HIM
RIGHT --

30:40.130 --> 30:41.961
YOU NEED TO SLOW DOWN
RIGHT NOW.

30:43.500 --> 30:46.207
START IN THERE.

30:46.240 --> 30:49.505
[ SIGHS ]

30:52.450 --> 30:54.418
YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT HAPPENED, RAY?

30:54.450 --> 30:56.509
[ SNIFFLING ]

30:56.550 --> 30:59.644
I STOLE IT
FROM MY OLD MAN.

30:59.690 --> 31:03.478
I WAS GOING TO GET IT BACK,
AND THEN HE FOUND OUT.

31:03.520 --> 31:07.229
SO I WENT TO BUY IT BACK,
AND IT WAS GONE.

31:07.260 --> 31:11.026
SO, WHAT IS THAT, EH?
IT HADN'T EVEN BEEN 30 DAYS.

31:11.070 --> 31:13.026
OKAY, WELL,
WHY IS THE RING SO SPECIAL?

31:13.070 --> 31:14.492
MY DAD HAS HAD TO BAIL ME
OUT OF JAIL.

31:14.540 --> 31:18.499
HE'S HAD TO WRESTLE ME
TO THE GROUND WHILE I WAS HIGH.

31:18.540 --> 31:21.634
HE'S HAD TO FIGHT MY BATTLES
WITH DRUG DEALERS.

31:21.680 --> 31:26.105
BUT I HAVE NEVER SEEN HIM CRY
UNTIL I DID THIS TO HIM.

31:26.150 --> 31:28.641
SO I DON'T EVEN CARE
WHAT HAPPENS TO ME --

31:28.680 --> 31:31.080
I JUST REALLY WANT HIM
TO GET HIS RING BACK.

31:31.120 --> 31:33.645
THIS IT?
YEAH.

31:37.320 --> 31:39.527
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU THIS,

31:39.560 --> 31:41.357
BUT YOU HAVE TO
PUT THE SWORD DOWN NOW.

31:43.260 --> 31:45.262
THIS IS WHAT
YOU CAME HERE FOR, RIGHT?

31:49.240 --> 31:51.208
BUT I HAVE TO
TAKE YOU IN.

31:51.240 --> 31:53.606
[ PANTING ]

31:53.640 --> 31:56.609
NOW, TURN AROUND.
PUT YOUR HANDS BEHIND YOUR BACK.

31:56.640 --> 31:59.507
[ HANDCUFFS CLICKING ]

32:03.180 --> 32:04.545
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

32:04.590 --> 32:08.151
IT WAS A 1918
ALLAN CUP HOCKEY RING --

32:08.190 --> 32:09.316
SPENCER'S GRANDFATHER'S.

32:09.360 --> 32:11.726
THE POOR DUMMY HAWKED IT
FOR 100 BUCKS.

32:11.760 --> 32:15.321
BILL POWER WAS SELLING IT ONLINE
FOR $10,000.
WOW.

32:15.360 --> 32:17.590
GUESS HE THOUGHT A DRUG ADDICT
WOULDN'T COME BACK FOR IT.

32:17.630 --> 32:20.428
IS IT WEIRD
THAT I FEEL SORRY FOR RAY?

32:20.470 --> 32:23.439
NO. THAT'S YOU.

32:23.470 --> 32:25.961
I SUPPOSE IT'S THE SAME REASON
YOU ENDED UP WITH HIM.

32:26.010 --> 32:28.979
YEAH,
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

32:29.010 --> 32:30.637
UH, THIS COULD BE
AN EIGHT-HOUR DAY.

32:30.680 --> 32:32.375
WHAT IS THE DEAL WITH
THIS EIGHT-HOUR-DAY THING?

32:32.410 --> 32:35.379
JUST TIRED
OF BREAKING PROMISES.

32:35.420 --> 32:37.376
YEAH.

32:37.420 --> 32:40.389
OKAY, LET'S GO BACK
AND WRITE IT DOWN...

32:40.420 --> 32:41.557
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

32:50.360 --> 32:51.725
I HAD IT UNDER CONTROL.

32:51.770 --> 32:54.068
NO, YOU DIDN'T.
I DID.

32:54.100 --> 32:56.432
IF I HADN'T HAVE WALKED
IN THERE WHEN I DID,

32:56.470 --> 32:57.732
YOU WOULD HAVE SHOT HIM.

32:57.770 --> 33:00.500
YOU WERE IN A RUSH,
WANTING TO BE A HERO.

33:00.540 --> 33:02.337
I WAS FOLLOWING PROTOCOL.
CALL ME.

33:02.380 --> 33:05.099
THAT'S WHAT
I TOLD YOU TO DO.

33:06.610 --> 33:09.317
YOU KNOW, I DON'T CARE
HOW GREAT YOU THINK YOU ARE.

33:09.350 --> 33:13.309
I DON'T CARE
WHO YOUR STEPDAD IS.

33:13.350 --> 33:15.580
I DON'T CARE Hga/V MANY EXCUSES

33:15.620 --> 33:18.180
OR PEANUTS YOU HAVE STUCK
IN YOUR THROAT.

33:18.230 --> 33:20.721
YOU ARE NOT READY TO BE
ON YOUR OWN IN THAT UNIFORM.

33:20.760 --> 33:22.728
YOU NEED ME.

33:22.760 --> 33:24.466
IF YOU DON'T LEAN ON ME,
YOU'RE GONNA FAIL.

33:24.500 --> 33:25.524
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

33:30.740 --> 33:32.708
[ SIGHS ]

33:32.740 --> 33:35.629
YOU GONNA WRITE ME UP?

33:35.680 --> 33:39.104
MAYBE. MAYBE NOT.

33:39.150 --> 33:41.516
DEPENDS.

33:41.550 --> 33:44.348
ON WHAT?
[ SEAT BELT CLICKS ]

33:44.390 --> 33:47.484
HOW MUCH YOU ANNOY ME
ON THE DRIVE HOME.

33:47.520 --> 33:50.216
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

33:50.260 --> 33:52.080
[ MONITOR BEEPS ]

33:52.130 --> 33:55.497
WHY DID --
WHY DID YOU COME, THEN?

33:55.530 --> 33:58.363
A COP SHOWED UP AT MY DOOR
AT MIDNIGHT,

33:58.400 --> 34:01.096
AND I THOUGHT
YOU WERE GONNA DIE.

34:01.140 --> 34:04.507
WELL...HERE I AM.

34:04.540 --> 34:05.768
I DIDN'T.

34:05.810 --> 34:07.630
AND YOU'RE STILL HERE.

34:07.670 --> 34:10.230
I DON'T KNOW, SAM.

34:10.280 --> 34:12.498
I GUESS I JUST THOUGHT
MAYBE THIS COULD BE

34:12.550 --> 34:16.111
AN OPPORTUNITY
FOR YOU TO BE OPEN.

34:16.150 --> 34:17.777
OPEN TO WHAT?

34:17.820 --> 34:21.153
[ SIGHS ]
TO US, TO THE FAMILY.

34:21.190 --> 34:23.112
YOU'RE -- [ CHUCKLES ]
YOU'RE CRAZY.

34:23.160 --> 34:24.184
[ SIGHS ]

34:24.230 --> 34:28.428
[ Chuckling ] OH, MAN,
CAN YOU EVER HOLD A GRUDGE.

34:30.600 --> 34:32.818
I ONLY GOT
THE BACKBONE GENE.

34:32.870 --> 34:35.293
YOUR ABILITY
TO TOLERATE MEN LIKE HIM

34:35.340 --> 34:36.534
IS, UM -- WELL,
IT'S AMAZING IS WHAT IT IS.

34:36.570 --> 34:38.538
GET OVER IT, SAM!

34:40.270 --> 34:43.137
HE'S OUR FATHER.

34:43.180 --> 34:44.704
WHO ART IN HEAVEN.

34:44.750 --> 34:47.605
SEE?
I DO KNOW A PRAYER.

34:50.180 --> 34:52.410
SQUARE, COME ON.
DON'T CALL ME THAT.

34:52.450 --> 34:53.781
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
DON'T CALL YOU THAT?

34:53.820 --> 34:55.117
I'VE ALWAYS
CALLED YOU THAT.

34:55.160 --> 34:57.253
WHEN WE WERE A FAMILY.
SARAH.

34:57.290 --> 34:58.325
KNOCK, KNOCK.

34:58.360 --> 34:59.782
WHO'S THERE?

35:06.100 --> 35:09.297
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

35:09.340 --> 35:10.830
HEY. HOW DID IT GO?
HEY.

35:10.870 --> 35:14.271
HEY. UM...
YEAH, IT WENT GREAT.

35:15.540 --> 35:18.441
HEY, UH, YOU GUYS, UH,
WANT TO TAKE A GROUP SHOT --

35:18.480 --> 35:19.845
YOU KNOW,
AFTER MY FIRST DAY?

35:19.880 --> 35:21.768
DO IT. YEAH, IT'S FINE.
SURE.

35:21.820 --> 35:24.243
HEY, I REALLY --
I REALLY WANT TO THANK YOU GUYS

35:24.290 --> 35:25.780
FOR BEING MY NEW FAMILY.

35:25.820 --> 35:28.380
IT -- IT MEANS A LOT.
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

35:28.420 --> 35:29.648
AND I WANT TO GIVE
AN INDIVIDUAL SHOUT-OUT

35:29.690 --> 35:32.682
TO MY T.O., M.C. NALLY.

35:32.730 --> 35:35.198
UM, YOU REALLY
HELPED ME OUT TODAY.

35:35.230 --> 35:38.165
AND TOMORROW, I'LL LISTEN
TO EVERY WORD YOU SAY.

35:38.200 --> 35:39.565
ALL GOOD.

35:39.600 --> 35:43.297
HEY, YOU GUYS -- YOU GUYS
WANT TO GET SOME DRINKS?

35:43.340 --> 35:45.262
OHH.
BOND?

35:45.310 --> 35:47.403
NO, IT'S BEEN A LONG DAY.
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

35:47.440 --> 35:49.772
YEAH, YOU KNOW, I GOT TO GET TO
THE HOSPITAL TO SEE CHLOE, SO...

35:49.810 --> 35:51.300
SORRY, MAN.
I'M WIPED.

35:51.350 --> 35:52.339
YEAH, THAT'S COOL.

35:52.380 --> 35:54.348
NO, I'M -- I'M --
I'M BUSY TONIGHT, TOO, ANYWAY,

35:54.380 --> 35:56.610
SO MAYBE TOMORROW.
YEAH.

35:56.650 --> 35:58.345
[ DOOR BUZZES ]

35:58.390 --> 36:00.381
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

36:02.960 --> 36:05.383
HEY, MEGHAN.

36:05.430 --> 36:06.920
HEY, IT'S OFFICER DIAZEPAM.

36:06.960 --> 36:09.258
YOU STILL FEEL LIKE
SOME COMPANY?

36:09.300 --> 36:10.824
GREAT. GREAT. ME, TOO.

36:10.860 --> 36:13.294
GOOD.
WHAT'S YOUR ADDRESS?

36:13.330 --> 36:15.434
I THINK I CAN.
I THINK I CAN.

36:15.470 --> 36:17.290
I KNEW YOU COULD.
[ LAUGHS ]

36:17.340 --> 36:19.831
I'LL CALL YOU LATER.
YEAH, ANYTIME.

36:19.870 --> 36:22.873
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

36:26.750 --> 36:28.968
[ SIGHS ]

36:29.020 --> 36:31.739
YOUR SMELL WOKE ME UP.

36:35.390 --> 36:38.723
I MISS MAKING DINNER
WITH YOU.

36:38.760 --> 36:40.978
ME, TOO,
WHICH IS STRANGE,

36:41.030 --> 36:43.419
CONSIDERING WE ONLY DID IT
A COUPLE TIMES.
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:43.460 --> 36:46.224
IT'S NOT LIKE
WE LIVED TOGETHER.

36:46.270 --> 36:48.636
IT'S NOT LIKE
WE'RE MARRIED.

36:50.500 --> 36:52.434
TOO SOON?

36:52.470 --> 36:54.870
NO.

36:57.780 --> 37:00.704
I KNOW THAT YOU WANT
AN EXPLANATION.

37:02.980 --> 37:06.689
OKAY,
HERE'S THE DEAL --

37:06.720 --> 37:10.417
NORMALLY, I'M LIKE A FUN,
MODERN-DAY INDIE FLICK.

37:10.460 --> 37:11.529
AGREE?

37:12.960 --> 37:14.518
OKAY.

37:14.560 --> 37:16.391
BUT WHEN I WAS WITH WES,

37:16.430 --> 37:21.538
I WAS THIS DARK,
DEPRESSING, PERIOD MOVIE,

37:21.570 --> 37:24.562
YOU KNOW, LIKE,
BEFORE THE SUFFRAGE MOVEMENT.

37:26.340 --> 37:30.299
THAT'S IT?

37:30.340 --> 37:31.841
THAT'S --
THAT'S YOUR EXPLANATION --

37:31.880 --> 37:34.417
A-A WEIRD MOVIE ANALOGY?
WHAT DOES THAT EVEN MEAN?

37:34.450 --> 37:37.942
I-I WAS TRYING TO PAINT
A PICTURE WITH MY WORDS.

37:42.460 --> 37:48.695
...HE WAS --
HE WAS JEALOUS AND POSSESSIVE,

37:48.730 --> 37:51.722
AND I LET MYSELF
BE CONTROLLED.

37:51.770 --> 37:55.297
AND I'M REALLY EMBARRASSED
ABOUT IT,

37:55.340 --> 37:58.332
WHICH IS WHY
I DIDN'T TELL YOU.

38:00.710 --> 38:03.702
LOOK...

38:06.610 --> 38:10.979
...WES AND I --
WE WEREN'T GOOD TOGETHER...

38:11.020 --> 38:14.319
BUT YOU AND I SO ARE,

38:14.360 --> 38:16.487
AND THAT'S
ALL THAT MATTERS.

38:21.430 --> 38:26.697
SO PLEASE SHUT UP AND KISS ME
BEFORE I DIE.

38:38.080 --> 38:40.378
WANTED TO CHECK IN
ON YOU.

38:40.410 --> 38:41.911
HOW WAS
YOUR FIRST DAY?

38:41.950 --> 38:44.510
YOU GET ALONG
WITH YOUR TRAINING OFFICER?

38:44.550 --> 38:47.519
UH, YEAH,
SHE'S -- SHE'S GREAT.

38:47.550 --> 38:49.415
YOU KNOW,
SHE'S -- SHE'S GREAT.

38:49.460 --> 38:52.782
IS THERE SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO TELL ME?

38:52.830 --> 38:55.799
NO, NO.

38:55.830 --> 38:58.526
TODAY WAS GOOD.

38:58.570 --> 39:00.390
I'M JUST, UH...

39:00.430 --> 39:02.660
JUST EAGER TO MAKE
A DIFFERENCE -- THAT'S ALL.

39:02.700 --> 39:04.099
AND I'M EAGER TO SEE
THAT HAPPEN.

39:04.140 --> 39:05.937
GOOD.

39:07.570 --> 39:11.404
WELL, UM,
I-I GOT TO GO.

39:11.450 --> 39:14.669
I'M, UH -- I'M MEETING
SOME OF THE GUYS FOR SOME BEERS,

39:14.720 --> 39:18.542
SO...I'LL SEE YOU.

39:20.850 --> 39:24.559
* OH, YOU KNOW,
WHEN YOU'RE ALONE *
TraCI: OH, COME ON!

39:24.590 --> 39:27.423
* I'M HOLDING ON
AND ON AND ON AND ON *
COME ON! COME ON!
WE CAN STILL MAKE IT!

39:27.460 --> 39:30.691
THE GAME CAN'T START WITHOUT
THEIR ROCK-'N'-ROLL LEFT WING,

39:30.730 --> 39:32.960
LEO "THE LION" NASH.
YEAH!

39:33.000 --> 39:34.695
LET'S GO.
YOU CAN DO IT!

39:34.740 --> 39:36.958
COME ON! COME ON! COME ON!
[ LAUGHS]

39:37.000 --> 39:38.968
* TO YOUR SOUL

39:39.010 --> 39:40.966
SO, TRAIN LEAVES
AT 8:00?

39:41.010 --> 39:43.831
[ SNIFFLES ] YEAH.
OKAY, GOOD. GOOD.

39:43.880 --> 39:46.440
WE STILL HAVE
QUITE A BIT OF TIME.

39:46.480 --> 39:48.573
I LIKE TO BUDGET LIKE
HALF AN HOUR TO GET ACROSS TOWN,

39:48.620 --> 39:50.838
YOU KNOW, JUST IN CASE
SOMETHING COMES UP --

39:50.880 --> 39:52.108
CONSTRUCTION, TRAFFIC.

39:52.150 --> 39:54.914
[ HORN HONKS ]
YOU NEVER KNOW.

39:54.960 --> 39:58.054
RIGHT, YEAH,
NO, IT'S GOOD TO, UM,

39:58.090 --> 40:00.627
BE ABLE TO TAKE OUR TIME.
MM-HMM.

40:00.660 --> 40:04.619
* SOUL SHINE

40:04.670 --> 40:06.490
UH, SAM'S GONNA MISS
HAVING YOU.

40:06.530 --> 40:09.897
WILL HE?

40:09.940 --> 40:12.909
[ SCOFFS ] I MEAN, YOU NEVER
KNOW WITH THAT GUY, RIGHT?

40:12.940 --> 40:15.636
DO YOU?
DO I WHAT?

40:18.210 --> 40:22.044
WHAT HE'S FEELING
FROM ONE MINUTE TO THE NEXT?

40:22.080 --> 40:26.642
I MEAN...HE SEEMS DIFFERENT
THESE LAST FEW WEEKS.

40:26.690 --> 40:29.716
AND HE SEEMS MORE OPEN.

40:29.760 --> 40:32.126
* I'M HOLDING ON
AND ON AND ON AND ON *
[ SIREN WAILING ]

40:32.160 --> 40:35.129
HMM.
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

40:35.160 --> 40:36.923
SAM WILL NEVER CHANGE.

40:36.960 --> 40:41.021
* TO YOUR SOUL

40:41.070 --> 40:45.632
